B[sr]
Dia.03 It is also 6 Points
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue255;\red255\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par What happens if White plays first?
\par If White throws-in at 1, Black two \'a1\'e3 stones are captured with snapback.
\par
\par How many points it is?
\par 2 captured stones makes 4 points plus 1 point at X, which means \cf1\b 5 points\cf0\b0 .
\par
\par If Black plays it is worth 1 point for Black, if White plays it is worth 5 points for White. Therefore B is worth \cf2\b 5+1=6\cf0\b0  points.
\par
\par \b A\b0  and \b B\b0  are both 6 points.
\par
\par
\par }
